trong>&quot;fake inverse kinematics&quot;.</strong> Based on paths drawn on the video he was able to generate a new video in which the tip of the baton would follow this path (see below), or as he writes: <em>&quot;directing the director&quot;.</em></p>\n<p>	<iframe frameborder=\"0\" height=\"320\" src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/9754197?title=0&amp;byline=0&amp;portrait=0&amp;color=ffffff\" width=\"400\"></iframe></p>\n<p>	Original footage can be seen here:&nbsp;<br />\n	<a href=\"http://vimeo.com/7772145\" title=\"http://vimeo.com/7772145\">http://vimeo.com/7772145</a></p>\n<p>	Nunos project page is here:<br />\n	<a href=\"http://projects.nunogodinho.com/2010/maestro\" title=\"http://projects.nunogodinho.com/2010/maestro\">http://projects.nunogodinho.com/2010/maestro</a></p>\n',1288108075,1288021675,'',0),('6:b3cd63bf40a91abc4caac26a5ad8c3f3','<h2>\n	About the Knowledgebase</h2>\n<p>	The main focus of this knowledge base will be to keep any useful resources we find and use in a central place. It will hopefully grow into both a reference and source of inspiration for us and later projects.</p>\n<p>	Some topics that should / could be covered here (feel free to add more) are:</p>\n',1288107118,1288020718,'',0),('6:22f0e50dba66d53b50d52ffcb437bae8','<p>Nuno Godinho has developed a very interessting software in <a href=\"/freelinking/VVVV\" class=\"freelinking\">VVVV</a> that plays with video-time in relation to what is show in the image.</p>\n',1288107451,1288021051,'',0),('6:d20db1af3543e7b5792a94994a3ab6f2','<p>Nuno Godinho has developed a very interessting software in <a href=\"/freelinking/VVVV\" class=\"freelinking\">VVVV</a> that plays with video-time in relation to what is show in the image.</p>\n<p>	Taking a video of a director he tracked the tip of his baton throughout the video. This produced a point cloud representing all possible positions that the tip has taken in regard to the video frame. For each point / pixel on the video frame he could find the c