e.echonest.com/</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://the.echonest.com/company/\">http://the.echonest.com/company/</a></p>\n<p>	The developer API provides:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n		Information on artists, songs, tracks</li>\n<li>\n		Allows to search for artists, songs</li>\n<li>\n		Allows to create playlists and catalogs</li>\n<li>\n		Allows to have songs identified</li>\n<li>\n		Will analyze tracks for musical information</li>\n</ul>\n<p>	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>	It is located at:&nbsp;<a href=\"\">http://developer.echonest.com/docs/v4/</a></p>\n',1288174581,1288088181,'',0),('6:872ce986bfbe09c7b7338aa0ce72af7e','<p>Echonest provides specialized services around music on the net:</p>\n<p>	<em>&quot;The Echo Nest is a music intelligence company founded by Tristan Jehan and Brian Whitman [...]. We grow an intelligence platform that automatically reads about and listens to the entire world of music for developers to build <strong>search, personalization and interactive music applications</strong>.&quot;</em></p>\n<p>	and</p>\n<p>	<em>&quot;Our applications are powered by a musical brain built at the Echo Nest along with years of research at UC Berkeley, Columbia and MIT. The musical brain automatically:</em></p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n		<em><strong>Reads about music</strong>, constantly analyzing millions of blog posts, reviews, playlists and discussion forums to understand how the online world describes every artist, album and song.</em></li>\n<li>\n		<em><strong>Listens to music</strong>, with technology actually listens to audio files, extracting musical attributes, such as tempo, instrumentation, key, time signature, energy, harmonic and timbral structures, to understand every song in similar ways a musician would describe it (e.g. &quot;heavy beat, swing groove, fast tempo, 4/4 time, key of B flat, mezzo piano&quot;).</em></li>\n<li>\n		<em><strong>Learns about music trends</strong>, analyzing the entire world of online music behavior &mdash; who&#39;s talking about which artists this week, what songs are being streamed and downloaded, etc. &mdash; to understand the latest trends, buzz and fan opinion.&quot;</em></li>\n</ol>\n<p>	See website at:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://the.echonest.com/\">http://the.echonest.com/</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://the.echonest.com/company/\">http://the.echonest.com/company/</a></p>\n<p>	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>	<strong>The developer API</strong> provides:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n		Information on artists, songs, tracks</li>\n<li>\n		Allows to search for artists, songs</li>\n<li>\n		Allows to create playlists and catalogs</li>\n<li>\n		Allows to have songs identified</li>\n<li>\n		Will analyze tracks for musical information</li>\n</ul>\n<p>	It is located at:&nbsp;<a href=\"\">http://developer.echonest.com/docs/v4/</a></p>\n',1288174613,1288088213,'',0),('6:a64f6c65b1fe2aec478fe8ab03bb7877','<p>Julia Opie, famous for his reduced &quot;illustrative&quot; drawings and scultures, started to make very elegant animations of <a href=\"http://www.julianopie.com/#/artwork/film/2009/162\">dancing people</a> (girls mostly) in 2003. Although the animations are very reduced he still manages to have the motion of the body transported very well.</p>\n',1288174665,1288088265,'',0);
